Future Improvements
The model could be improved with further feature engineering. The two top-of-mind:
Factor in the previous pitch. Some pitches are considered set-up pitches. For example, a pitcher could throw a fastball high and tight on the hitter then throw the next a breaking pitch low and outside. The difference in speed, movement, and location could make the pitch even more effective.
All movement is not created equally. A fastball that moves 8 inches might be a large amount of movement for a fastball but when compared to a curveball doesn’t move at all. Scale movement using the release point, speed, and pitch type.
Future Analysis
Analyze the best pitcher outings based on pitch quality.
Top batters in swinging at quality pitches.

